SIMPLE: impiety
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impiety
<hw>Im*pi"e*ty</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m*p⟦imac⟧"⟦esl⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Impieties</plw>
<pr>(⟦icr⟧m*p⟦imac⟧"⟦esl⟧*t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>impietas</ets>, fr. <ets>impius</ets> impious; cf. F.
<ets>impi⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Impious</er>,
<er>Piety</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being impious;
lack of piety; irreverence toward the Supreme Being; ungodliness;
wickedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An impious act; an act of wickedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those <qex>impieties</qex> for the which they are now visited.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ungodliness; irreligion; unrighteousness;
sinfulness; profaneness; wickedness; godlessness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impignorate</ent>⟦br⟧
